# OpenLabel — Member 2: The Engine Room

Build the FastAPI backend that serves as the central nervous system connecting the Flutter App (Member 1) ↔ AI Brain (Member 3) ↔ Supabase Database.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **API Keys Required** — Before running the server, you will need to provide:
> 1. `SUPABASE_URL` — Your Supabase project URL
> 2. `SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` — Public anon key for RLS-protected operations
> 3. `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` — Service role key for admin operations
> 4. `GEMINI_API_KEY` — Google Gemini API key for the AI analysis pipeline
>
> These will be stored in a `.env` file (git-ignored).

> [!WARNING]
> **Supabase Project Prerequisite** — You must have a Supabase project created with the provided SQL schema already executed. The backend will connect to it, not create the tables.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Decision: OCR Strategy** — For image-based label analysis, should we:
> - **Option A (Recommended):** Use Gemini 2.0 Flash's native vision capabilities (send image directly to Gemini, no separate OCR needed)
> - **Option B:** Use a dedicated OCR service (Tesseract/Google Vision) first, then pipe text to Gemini
>
> Option A is simpler, cheaper, and more accurate for food labels. Please confirm.

