### Services Layer

#### [NEW] [services/scraper.py](file:///c:/Users/kunal/Desktop/OpenLabel/services/scraper.py)
Web scraper for e-commerce product pages:
- Uses `httpx` (async) + `BeautifulSoup4` for HTML parsing
- Extracts: product name, ingredient list, nutrition info, price, FSSAI number
- Site-specific parsers for major Indian platforms:
  - BigBasket, Blinkit, Amazon.in, Flipkart, JioMart
- Fallback generic parser for unknown sites
- Proper User-Agent headers and rate limiting

#### [NEW] [services/ai_engine.py](file:///c:/Users/kunal/Desktop/OpenLabel/services/ai_engine.py)
Gemini 2.0 Flash integration:
- `analyze_image(image_bytes)` — Direct vision analysis of food label images
- `analyze_text(extracted_text, osint_context)` — Text-based analysis with OSINT enrichment
- Both methods use the full Tech-Justice system prompt from Member 3
- Returns `OpenLabelReport` Pydantic model via structured output
- Handles retries and error fallbacks

#### [NEW] [services/fssai_validator.py](file:///c:/Users/kunal/Desktop/OpenLabel/services/fssai_validator.py)
FSSAI license number validator:
- Format validation (14 digits, structure check)
- Decodes: license type (digit 1), state code (digits 2-3), year (digits 4-5)
- Online verification via FoSCoS portal scraping (best-effort)
- Returns validation status + decoded metadata

#### [NEW] [services/osint_data.py](file:///c:/Users/kunal/Desktop/OpenLabel/services/osint_data.py)
OSINT wholesale price reference:
- Loads `wholesale_prices.json` with commodity reference prices
